    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "739ae6bb_d1a2b29a",
        "filename": "src/gpu/GrStagingBufferManager.h",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 24,
      "author": {
        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-30T22:20:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So it is detaching the buffers from the GrStagingBufferManager. The dawn implementation happens to then store them on the GrDawnStagingBufferManager in the busy list, but if you look at the vulkan implemenation the ownership is passed on to a GrVkCommandBuffer. The dawn implemenation could also very easy decide to store its busy list on the GrDawnGpu instead.\n\nAnother way to think about it is the base class here, GrStagingBufferManager, is the cache and provider of staging slices for the GrGpu to use in a frame. The GrGpu then takes ownership of them as they are used on the gpu. It is then the backends decision whether it wants to give the buffers back to the manager to reuse or it has the option of just throwing them away.",
      "parentUuid": "0c618849_6f77a42f",
      "revId": "2c79e1f0850ca11c2bd56733f80694f54a0ca99e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7ff38706_5f6a2c7f",
        "filename": "src/gpu/GrStagingBufferManager.h",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 37,
      "author": {
        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-30T19:16:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Instead of passing in the mapPtr to this call (and the buffers constructor), we could make a map() virtual on GrStagingBuffer. The manager would call map() here and when it creates a new buffer. We\u0027d probably want an equivalent virtual unmap() if we do that which we\u0027d call here in the base during detachStagedBuffers(). I picked this route cause it avoids needing the extra virtuals on GrStagingBuffer and some implementations may not need to actually do the mapping and unmapping (obviously those one could just do nothing in the virtual calls).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 37,
        "startChar": 71,
        "endLine": 37,
        "endChar": 83
      },
      "revId": "2c79e1f0850ca11c2bd56733f80694f54a0ca99e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
