      "lineNbr": 34,
      "author": {
        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-30T22:20:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "First this did remind me that I left SK_DECLARE_INTERNAL_LLIST_INTERFACE(GrStagingBuffer) in the code. I don\u0027t really want to add that GrStagingBuffer, but I\u0027d be happy to add it for dawn only here. The awkward thing would be how dawn manages the ownership of the staging buffer. When we, as it currently is called, detach the buffers dawn has to hold the ownership. I guess we can call release on the unique_ptr to get a raw pointer, then add that to the list. Then when we recycle the buffer dawn just needs to re-wrap back into a unique_ptr. We would have to remember if we ever need to delete the list that still has buffers to call delete on them. However, that should never be case and we should only ever delete buffers in available or active.\n\nOkay talking this out, it sounds like it can work well. I\u0027ll give it a shot.",
      "parentUuid": "d5a5b00a_3965f53d",
